    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meal 1:</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into wedges, add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 5-8 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-peri-peri-chicken-and-caesar-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>peri peri spice mix</strong> with your<strong> honey</strong>,<strong> </strong>the juice<strong> </strong>of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, then give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>honey peri peri marinade</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> chicken thighs </strong>to the marinade and give it a good mix up until fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>marinated chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-peri-peri-chicken-and-caesar-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the wedges have had an initial 5-8 min, add the <strong>marinated chicken</strong> to the other side of the tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 17-18 min, or until the wedges are crispy and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>honey & peri peri chicken and wedges tray bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-peri-peri-chicken-and-caesar-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with the <strong>remaining lemon juice</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>,<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>lemon mayo</strong></p><p>Once everything has 8 min remaining, boil a little water in a kettle and trim your<strong> green beans</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>trimmed green beans </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with a small knob of<strong> butter</strong>, your <strong>grated garlic</strong>,<strong> </strong>a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a splash of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 7-8 min or until the green beans are tender with a bite \u2013 these are your <strong>garlicky green beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-peri-peri-chicken-and-caesar-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve <strong>half</strong> the <strong>honey peri-peri chicken</strong> (you'll eat the rest tomorrow!) with the<strong> wedges</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>garlicky green beans </strong>to the side with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lemon mayo</strong> (you'll use the rest tomorrow!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p><p>Cool the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>honey peri-peri chicken</strong> quickly (within 2 hours max) and refrigerate with the <strong>remaining lemon mayo</strong> in covered containers. Enjoy within 24 hours</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-peri-peri-chicken-and-caesar-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meal 2:</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining lemon mayo</strong> with your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Add a splash of <strong>cold water</strong>,<strong> </strong>a little drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> and a generous grind of<strong> pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Caesar dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-peri-peri-chicken-and-caesar-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>glorious grains</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p><p>Combine the <strong>warmed grains</strong> with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>Caesar dressing </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a large bowl, then add the <strong>chopped lettuce</strong> and toss until well combined \u2013 this is your <strong>Caesar grain salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-peri-peri-chicken-and-caesar-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>honey peri-peri chicken </strong>and serve over the <strong>Caesar grain salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle with the <strong>remaining Caesar dressing </strong>and sprinkle over the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
